  "prompt": "Is there a survey app which pays at least 5 dollars for easy questions?",
  "response": "While there are survey apps that offer payments, finding one that consistently pays $5 or more per survey is rare. Some legitimate survey apps include:\n\n1. Swagbucks\n2. Survey Junkie\n3. Respondent.io\n4. Prolific\n5. UserTesting\n6. Vindale Research\n\nMost survey apps typically pay between $0.50 to $3 per survey. To maximize earnings:\n- Sign up for multiple survey platforms\n- Complete your profile accurately\n- Check for surveys frequently\n- Be honest in your responses\n\nKeep in mind:\n- Earnings can be inconsistent\n- Some apps have minimum payout thresholds\n- Not all surveys will qualify you\n- Payments are usually via PayPal or gift cards\n\nRealistic expectations are important. These apps can provide some extra pocket money, but they're unlikely to be a significant income source.",
